    Cellosaurus Querying PubChem with AnnotationGx

    cell_model_passports_models is a preprocessed version of the cell model passports dataset

    cell_model_passports_models.Rd

    A preprocessed version of the cell model passports dataset. This dataset contains the following columns: CMP.model_id, CMP.sampleid, CMP.model_name, CMP.cancer_type_ncit_id, CMP.COSMIC_ID, CMP.BROAD_ID, CMP.CCLE_ID, and CMP.RRID. This dataset is used in the AnnotationGx package to map cell line names from various sources to the Cellosaurus database.

    Usage

    data(cell_model_passports_models)

    Format

    A data table with 8 columns and 1001 rows.

    CMP.model_id

    char The model id of the cell line in the cell model passports dataset.

    CMP.sample_id

    char The sample id of the cell line in the cell model passports dataset.

    CMP.model_name

    char The name of the cell line in the cell model passports dataset.

    CMP.cancer_type_ncit_id

    char The cancer type ncit id of the cell line in the cell model passports dataset.

    CMP.COSMIC_ID

    int The COSMIC ID of the cell line in the cell model passports dataset.

    CMP.BROAD_ID

    int The BROAD ID of the cell line in the cell model passports dataset.

    CMP.CCLE_ID

    int The CCLE ID of the cell line in the cell model passports dataset.

    CMP.RRID

    char The RRID of the cell line in the cell model passports dataset.

    Source

    https://cog.sanger.ac.uk/cmp/download/model_list_20240103.csv

    Examples

    data(cell_model_passports_models)
